</table>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="700">2.2. Editing a property</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can find properties in the menu <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Configuration</strong>. You can modify the settings described in <a href="#table-create-variation-property">Table 3</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a property:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Configuration</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong> to see all properties.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> Select filters to limit the search results.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the property.<br>
→ The <strong>General</strong> tab opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Edit the settings. Note <a href="#table-edit-variation-property">Table 4</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save"></i></span>) the settings.</p>
