<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="900">2.4. Deleting a property</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can delete one or more properties at the same time.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="1000">2.4.1. Deleting a property</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to irreversibly delete a property if it is no longer needed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting a property:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Configuration</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Select filters to limit the search results.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Start the search.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the property.<br>
→ The detail view of the property opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete property</strong>.<br>
→ A window opens and you need to confirm your decision.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ The property is deleted and removed from the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="1100">2.4.2. Deleting multiple properties</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to irreversibly delete multiple properties if they are no longer needed.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deleting multiple properties:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Configuration</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Select filters to limit the search results.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Start the search.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the properties that you want to delete.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ A window opens and you need to confirm your decision.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Delete</strong>.<br>
→ The selected properties are deleted and removed from the overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="1200">2.5. Grouping properties</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Create property groups to summarise multiple properties. Proceed as described below to create a property group.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a property group:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Groups</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add property group</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings. Note <a href="#table-create-variation-property-group">Table 6</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save"></i></span>) the settings.<br>
→ The property group is created.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
